{{Orphan|date=November 2010}}

'''Boyer Glacier''' ({{Coord|73|18|S|167|21|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a short tributary [[glacier]] situated {{convert|10|nmi|km|0}} west of [[Index Point]] in the eastern part of the [[Mountaineer Range]]. It flows north into lower [[Mariner Glacier]], [[Victoria Land]]. It was mapped by the [[United States Geological Survey]] from surveys and from [[U.S. Navy]] air photos, 1960–64, and named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for [[Jack W. Boyer]], a U.S. Navy radioman at [[Hallett Station]], 1962.<ref name=gnis/>

