In [[biochemistry]], a '''glycolytic oscillation''' is the repetitive fluctuation of in the concentrations of [[metabolite]]s,<ref name="chandra">{{Cite journal | last1 = Chandra | first1 = F. A. | last2 = Buzi | first2 = G. | last3 = Doyle | first3 = J. C. | authorlink3 = John Doyle (engineer)| doi = 10.1126/science.1200705 | title = Glycolytic Oscillations and Limits on Robust Efficiency | journal = [[Science (journal)|Science]]| volume = 333 | issue = 6039 | pages = 187–192 | year = 2011 | pmid = 21737735| url = http://www.sciencemag.org/content/333/6039/187.abstract| pmc = }}</ref> classically observed experimentally in yeast and muscle.<ref>{{Cite book | last1 = Goldbeter | first1 = A. | last2 = Berridge | first2 = M. J. | doi = 10.1017/CBO9780511608193.005 | chapter = Oscillatory enzymes: simple periodic behaviour in an allosteric model for glycolytic oscillations | title = Biochemical Oscillations and Cellular Rhythms | pages = 31–88| year = 1996 | isbn = 9780511608193 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref> The first observations of oscillatory behaviour in glygolysis were made by Duysens and Amesz in 1957.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Duysens | first1 = L. N. M. | last2 = Amesz | first2 = J. | doi = 10.1016/0006-3002(57)90141-5 | title = Fluorescence spectrophotometry of reduced phosphopyridine nucleotide in intact cells in the near-ultraviolet and visible region | journal = [[Biochimica et Biophysica Acta]]| volume = 24 | issue = 1 | pages = 19–26 | year = 1957 | pmid = 13426197| pmc = }}</ref>
The problem of modelling glycolytic oscillation has been studied in [[control theory]] and [[dynamical systems]] since the 1960s<ref name="chandra" /> since the behaviour depends on the rate of [[enzyme substrate (biology)|substrate]] injection. Early models used two variables, but the most complex behaviour they could demonstrate was period oscillations due to the [[Poincaré–Bendixson theorem]], so later models introduced further variables.<ref>{{Cite book | doi = 10.1142/9789814374439_0013 | first = C. | last = Letellier| chapter = Chaos in Biology and Biomedicine | title = Chaos in Nature | series = World Scientific Series on Nonlinear Science Series A | volume = 81 | pages = 277–322 | year = 2013 | isbn = 978-981-4374-42-2 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>
