{{Taxobox | name = Père David's mole<ref name=msw3>{{MSW3 Hutterer | pages = 309}}</ref> | status = DD | trend = unknown | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = <ref>{{cite journal|author=Kryštufek, B.|author2=Amori, G.|last-author-amp=yes|title=''Talpa davidiana''|journal=[[IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]]|volume=2008|page=e.T135458A4129356|publisher=[[IUCN]]|year=2008|url=http://oldredlist.iucnredlist.org/details/135458/0|doi=10.2305/IUCN.UK.2008.RLTS.T135458A4129356.en|accessdate=8 September 2016}}</ref> | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Chordata]] | classis = [[Mammal]]ia | ordo = [[Eulipotyphla]] | familia = [[Talpidae]] | genus = ''[[Talpa (genus)|Talpa]]'' | species = '''''T. davidiana''''' | binomial = ''Talpa davidiana'' | binomial_authority = ([[Henri Milne-Edwards|Milne-Edwards]], 1884) | synonyms = ''Talpa streeti'' | range_map = Pere David's Mole area.png | range_map_caption = Père David's mole range }}
'''Père David's mole''' (''Talpa davidiana'') is a [[mole (animal)|mole]] found only in [[Kurdistan Province, Iran|Kurdistan Province]], [[Iran]]. It is listed as a data deficient species. The species is named after the zoologist [[Armand David]]. As ''T. streeti'', it is known as the Persian mole.
