'''Qiwam al-Din Muhammad al-Hasani''' was a [[Iran|Persian]] physician of the late 17th century. Hasani was a scholar who is known to have been working in the city of [[Qazvin]] in Persia in the year 1694 CE. The [[National Library of Medicine]] has in its collections a rare copy of a collection of five Arabic poems concerned with [[medicine]], [[astronomy]], [[arithmetic]], [[calligraphy]], and proper conduct. These five poems were collectively titled ''al-Khamsah al-Qazwiniyah'' (The Five Qazwini works). The copy at NLM was copied by a professional scribe for the author, whose stamps are in the volume, next to a statement that he corrected the volume in the year 1719–1720 CE. Thus we learn from this volume that Qiwan al-Din Muhammad al-Hasani was still working by 1719 CE.
